comments: Morris Sr. (LAC) is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Batum (LAC) makes clean contact with the ball as marginal contact occurs with Doncic's (DAL) side during the inbound.
Powell (DAL) jumps toward George (LAC) and marginal body contact occurs as George secures the rebound.
Jackson (LAC) engages and disengages with Hardaway Jr. (DAL) as Hardaway Jr. moves to set the pick.
George (LAC) extends his left hand and marginal contact occurs with Hardaway Jr.'s (DAL) left arm prior to his gather.
Jackson (LAC) moves forward toward Powell (DAL) and marginal contact occurs with Powell's front as he is passing.
George (LAC) briefly has his arm around Powell's (DAL) upper half before quickly sliding it off.
George (LAC) has his left arm extended outward and marginal contact occurs with Doncic's (DAL) front as Doncic starts his dribble.
Powell (DAL) initiates contact across Leonard's (LAC) left arm after his gather that affects his shot attempt.
Morris Sr. (LAC) extends his left arm into Kleber's (DAL) path and initiates contact to Kleber's front that affects his SQBR as he cuts into the lane.
Mann (LAC) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Kleber (DAL) as he receives the pass.
Doncic (DAL) jumps vertically alongside Mann's (LAC) path and absorbs the marginal body contact that occurs at the end of the drive.
Doncic (DAL) maintains verticality and absorbs the contact made with Batum (LAC) during his upward shooting motion.
Finney-Smith (DAL) and Batum (LAC) make incidental body contact with one another as they each attempt to retrieve the rebound.
Morris Sr. (LAC) commits a take foul on Hardaway Jr. (DAL).
Finney-Smith (DAL) legally contests Leonard's (LAC) jump shot attempt.
After initially engaging with one another as the shot is released, Jackson (LAC) grabs and pulls Richardson's (DAL) left arm during rebounding.
Kleber (DAL) maintains a rested forearm on Leonard's (LAC) side and marginal contact occurs as Leonard mishandles the pass.
